<HL>
   Wharf (Holdings) Profit Rises
</HL>
<DATE>
08/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   H.WHF
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   HONG KONG -- Wharf (Holdings) Ltd., the investment holding
company in the shipping magnate Y.K. Pao's corporate empire,
said its profit for the year ended March 31 grew 12% to 1.25
billion Hong Kong dollars (US$160.8 million), or 65.7 Hong
Kong cents a share, from HK$1.11 billion, or 59 cents a
share, a year earlier. Revenue increased 11% to HK$3.12
billion from HK$2.82 billion.
   Directors proposed a final dividend of 33 cents a share,
increasing the full-year payout 17% to 43.5 cents from 37.3
cents a year earlier.
</LP>
