<HL>
   Who's News:
   Jack Henry Chief Resigns
</HL>
<DATE>
08/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   JKHY WNEWS
</CO>
<LP>
   MONETT, Mo. -- Jack Henry &amp; Associates Inc. said that
Colin McAllister resigned as chief executive officer,
executive vice president and a director. The company didn't
explain the resignation, and officials couldn't be reached
for comment.
   The company, which markets and installs data-processing
software systems at financial institutions, said Jerry Hall,
president, has assumed Mr. McAllister's duties, effective
immediately.
</LP>
