   Business Brief -- APL Corp.:
   Posner-Controlled Company
   Misses Payments on Debt
</HL>
<DATE>
08/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2
</SO>
<CO>
   APL
</CO>
<IN>
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
</IN>
<LP>
   APL Corp. said it missed a total of $4.1 million in debt
payments due yesterday, permitting its creditors to declare
about $27.1 million of principal outstanding "immediately due
and payable" in 30 days.
   APL, controlled by Miami financier Victor Posner, said
such a declaration would also trigger the acceleration of
payment obligations on $8 million of other debt. It said it
is negotiating with debt holders "concerning the cure or
other satisfaction" of the payments it missed yesterday.
