<HL>
   Who's News:
   Entergy Corp. Realigns
   Management as Part
   Of Cost-Cutting Plan
</HL>
<DATE>
08/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   ETR WNEWS
</CO>
<LP>
   NEW ORLEANS -- Entergy Corp. said it realigned its
management, expanding the duties of four senior executives,
as part of a cost-cutting plan.
   The utility holding company said Jack L. King, its
50-year-old senior vice president, operations, becomes
executive vice president, operations, of the company's
Entergy Services Inc. unit. Donald Hunter, 56, president and
chief operating officer of the company's Louisiana Power &amp;
Light Co. and New Orleans Public Service Inc. units, will
become a senior vice president of the Entergy Services unit.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Hunter will be succeeded by Donald E. Meiners, 54,
president and chief executive of Entergy Services. Jerry D.
Jackson, 45, a former senior vice president at both Entergy
and Entergy Services, was named executive vice president,
finance and external affairs, of the parent and the unit.
   Edwin A. Lupberger remains chairman and chief executive
officer of Entergy.
