<LP>
   BSN Corp. said that PaineWebber Inc. is soliciting offers
to buy all or parts of the assets of the Dallas sporting
goods manufacturer. BSN expects the offers to exceed the
company's book value of $9.20 a share.
   BSN's board already has rejected unsolicited offers that
it considered inadequate. Houston-based Pelham Investment
Associates Limited Partnership has acquired 7.3% of the
company's shares and has sought to buy a controlling
interest.
</LP>
